result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) and Operating w/ PAC (4th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Aaron R Hubbell was found guilty of OWI (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Aaron R Hubbell in court with attorney Bruce Patrick Anderson.  Angela Lynn Beranek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights presented.  Court questions defendant.  
State presents 2nd Amended Information.  State moves to amend Count 1 OWI 4th (misdemeanor). 
Defendant pleads guilty to Count 1 as amended.  Court accepts guilty plea and finds guilty on Count 1 as amended.
Court orders Count 2 dismissed.  
State relates recommendation.  Attorney Anderson relates recommendation.
Court questions defendant.

Court relates and orders:
$600.00 fine plus costs - 60 DTP or may set up payment plan.  
Jail: 60 days with huber and good time - 1 day credit.  After 48 hours, may serve in St.Croix County if no cost to Barron County. 
Driver's License Revocation: 24 Months.
Ignition Interlock Device: 24 Months.
AODA and comply with recommended follow-up treatment.  

Attorney Anderson requests firearm that was in vehicle when defendant arrested be returned to owner.  No objection by State.  Court orders Sheriff's Department to return firearm to Kara Bray forewith.  

Defendant must report to jail by 12:00 p.m. today.
Jury trial on July 14, 2015 at 08:00 am.
